<page_title>Seeing the Debye Radius</page_title>
<text>Seeing the Debye Radius

By Eric Rosenbaum, Massachusetts Institute of Technology

 

 

A charged particle exerts a force on nearby charged particles.  Particles further away are &quot;screened&quot; by the ones in between, and don&apos;t feel the force. The debye radius is the distance within which a particle feels the force.  Outside the radius, they are unaffected.

In this model, you can set the charge on a blue particle, surrounded by other charged particles.  

Can you see the size of the debye radius changing as you change the charge?</text>
